
We can add multiple classes to an HTML elementâ€™s class 
attribute by separating them with a space. This enables 
us to mix and match CSS classes to create many unique 
styles without writing a custom class for every style 
combination needed.


HTML
<h1 class='green bold'> ... </h1>
<h2 class='bold'>...</h2>


CSS 
.green {
  color: green;
}
 
.bold {
  font-weight: bold;
}